
@startuml

' Define classes
class Student {
  +String studentID
  +String name
  +List<Course> coursesRegistered
  +requestAppointment(Course, TeachingAssistant): Appointment
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  +String taID
  +String name
  +List<Course> coursesTaught
  +scheduleAppointment(Student, Course): Appointment
}

class Course {
  +String courseId
  +String title
  +List<Student> studentsEnrolled
  +List<TeachingAssistant> tasAssigned
}

class Appointment {
  +String appointmentId
  +DateTime timeSlot
  +Student student
  +TeachingAssistant teachingAssistant
  +Course course
}

' Relationships
Student "1" -- "0..*" Course : registered for
Student "1" -- "0..1" Appointment : has

TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Course : teaches
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : provides

Course "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : has appointments for
Course "1" -- "0..*" Student : has enrolled students
Course "1" -- "0..*" TeachingAssistant : has TAs

Appointment "1" -- "1" Student : involves
Appointment "1" -- "1" TeachingAssistant : involves
Appointment "1" -- "1" Course : related to

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **Student**: Can register for multiple courses and request appointments.
- **TeachingAssistant (TA)**: Teaches one or more courses and schedules appointments with students.
- **Course**: Has enrolled students and assigned TAs. Appointments are made per course.
- **Appointment**: A scheduled meeting between a student and a TA for a specific course.

The constraints from the requirement are reflected in the relationships:
- A student can only request an appointment for a course they're enrolled in.
- A TA can only schedule appointments for courses they teach.
- Each appointment is for one course, one TA, and one student.

